== Use Case 6: The "I'm Cooking for One" Reality

_Situation:_ You live alone. Recipes serve 4–6. You end up with too many scraps or too much food.

_Drain Salad strategy:_

+ _Embrace small batches:_ Most Drain Salad recipes scale down easily. Make 1 serving of pasta with crumbs. Make a 2-egg frittata in a small pan.

+ _Freeze in portions:_ If you make a batch of soup or gratin, portion it into single servings and freeze. Future you will appreciate this.

+ _Use scraps for condiments:_ One person doesn't generate enough scraps for a daily salad, but you can accumulate them over a week and make ferments or relishes that last months.

_Why this works:_ Cooking for one is about systems, not recipes. Build a system where scraps accumulate into something useful over time.

